The 'Tilefish' (Lopholatilus chamaeleonticeps) is one of several species and the
largest in the family Malacanthidae.<ref name = "AbleBS">Able, K. W. 2002.
Tilefishes. Family Malacanthidae. In Bigelow and Schroeder’s fishes of the Gulf
of Maine, 3rd ed. (B. B. Collette and G. Klein-MacPhee, eds.), p. 397–400.
Smithsonian Inst. Press, Washington, D.C.</ref><ref name = "AFS29">Nelson, J.
S., and coauthors. 2004. Common and Scientific Names of Fishes from the United
States, Canada, and Mexico, 6th ed., Special Publication 29. American Fisheries
Society, Bethesda, MD.</ref> It is often marketed as a food fish under the label
“golden tilefish”.<ref name = "NMFS">http://www.fishwatch.gov/seafood_profiles/-
species/tilefish/species_pages/golden_tilefish.htm</ref>
